[The nature of the intensive care offered the 242 rabies victims is
not stated. Hopefully this includes post-exposure vaccination
otherwise the prospects for the patients are grim. There appears to be
an unfortunate lack of coordination between the medical and the
veterinary authorities in the province.

East Nusa Tenggara is a province of Indonesia, located in the eastern
portion of the Lesser Sunda Islands, including West Timor. The
provincial capital is Kupang, located on West Timor. The province
consists of about 550 islands, but is dominated by the 3 main islands
of Flores, Sumba, and West Timor, the western half of the island of
Timor. A map of the Indonesia island of East Nusa Tenggara can be
accessed at:
<http://www.nusa-tenggara.com/east/html/map-ntt.html>. - Mod.CP]
